00:39:52.040 --> 00:39:53.710
Advancing the

00:39:53.720 --> 00:39:58.470
resolution is a sign of growing

00:39:58.480 --> 00:40:01.430
frustration with the war. Now, will they

00:40:01.440 --> 00:40:02.830
do it? I don't know. So, do you think

00:40:02.840 --> 00:40:03.870
they're going to block it, Braden? What

00:40:03.880 --> 00:40:06.270
do you all think? Tell me. Do you think

00:40:06.280 --> 00:40:07.830
that they're going to end up making it

00:40:07.840 --> 00:40:09.870
where Trump can't make these decisions?

00:40:09.880 --> 00:40:11.710
Tell me in the comments down below. Do

00:40:11.720 --> 00:40:13.030
you think that they're going to end up

00:40:13.040 --> 00:40:15.270
blocking him

00:40:15.280 --> 00:40:16.670
and saying,

00:40:16.680 --> 00:40:18.110
'We're not going to allow you to do this

00:40:18.120 --> 00:40:20.190
anymore. We're calling you back home.

00:40:20.200 --> 00:40:22.910
Cuba's next.'Well, what happens

00:40:22.920 --> 00:40:24.550
with all this? I'm curious where

00:40:24.560 --> 00:40:27.110
everybody's at with that. I saw Israel

00:40:27.120 --> 00:40:32.190
finishing the job.

00:40:32.200 --> 00:40:35.990
So, let's see what happens.

00:40:37.560 --> 00:40:39.630
Do you remember, Braden? Yes, I

00:40:39.640 --> 00:40:41.350
remember that. I say Israel

00:40:41.360 --> 00:40:46.350
finishes the job. America will not.

00:40:46.360 --> 00:40:49.110
We will save face trying to inject the

00:40:49.120 --> 00:40:52.510
economy with a great stimulus. And I

00:40:52.520 --> 00:40:53.790
saw a

00:40:53.790 --> 00:40:53.800
stimulus

00:40:53.800 --> 00:40:55.990
being passed around for

00:40:56.000 --> 00:40:59.550
households underneath $150,000,

00:40:59.560 --> 00:41:01.590
saying, 'Listen, if you make this

00:41:01.600 --> 00:41:02.710
amount, we're going to give you a

00:41:02.720 --> 00:41:03.950
certain amount of money for your

00:41:03.950 --> 00:41:03.960
household,'trying

00:41:03.960 --> 00:41:05.910
to get people to be

00:41:05.920 --> 00:41:07.630
excited.

00:41:07.640 --> 00:41:11.270
But let's see what happens.

00:41:11.270 --> 00:41:11.280
The

00:41:11.280 --> 00:41:14.710
US Senate advises a resolution to curb

00:41:14.720 --> 00:41:27.590
Trump's power to wage war on Iran.

00:41:27.600 --> 00:41:31.310
It's interesting to me.

00:41:31.320 --> 00:41:33.430
So I believe that's where we are.

00:41:33.440 --> 00:41:34.830
So we will continue to pray for

00:41:34.840 --> 00:41:36.710
President Trump. We will pray for

00:41:36.720 --> 00:41:38.310
President Trump and the peace that

00:41:38.320 --> 00:41:40.470
passes all understanding over Jerusalem,

00:41:40.480 --> 00:41:41.670
over

00:41:41.680 --> 00:41:43.510
all the things that we know to keep

00:41:43.520 --> 00:41:46.070
doing. Standing in the gap, praying for

00:41:46.080 --> 00:41:48.590
our nation, praying for revival. These

00:41:48.590 --> 00:41:48.600
are

00:41:48.600 --> 00:41:50.430
the main things I was

00:41:50.440 --> 00:41:51.830
thinking about today as I was taking

00:41:51.840 --> 00:41:53.110
care of the kids and doing things and

00:41:53.120 --> 00:41:56.910
helping out with Diana.

00:41:56.920 --> 00:41:58.390
I said, 'Lord,

00:41:58.400 --> 00:42:00.750
we always talk about revival and we

00:42:00.760 --> 00:42:04.110
always reflect on John

00:42:04.120 --> 00:42:07.670
G. Lake and Smith Wigglesworth and that

00:42:07.680 --> 00:42:09.630
was not our generation.

00:42:09.640 --> 00:42:12.070
Kathryn Kuhlman kind of was,

00:42:12.080 --> 00:42:15.270
and Oral Roberts, and Jack Coe, and

00:42:15.280 --> 00:42:17.590
William Branham and

00:42:17.590 --> 00:42:17.600
them.

00:42:17.600 --> 00:42:21.310
We see, we hear, and we have

00:42:21.320 --> 00:42:23.910
videos on YouTube that we reflect

00:42:23.910 --> 00:42:23.920
on

00:42:23.920 --> 00:42:26.670
and go, 'Wow,'but I'm so tired of

00:42:26.680 --> 00:42:31.110
talking about the past.

00:42:31.120 --> 00:42:33.110
As much as I honor those people and I go,

00:42:33.120 --> 00:42:34.710
'Wow, it would have been really cool to be

00:42:34.720 --> 00:42:36.190
there.'What

00:42:36.200 --> 00:42:39.670
about today and what about now?

00:42:39.680 --> 00:42:41.950
I said, 'Lord, what about today?'I'm

00:42:41.950 --> 00:42:41.960
sitting here

00:42:41.960 --> 00:42:43.710
trying to find old things

00:42:43.720 --> 00:42:45.790
from Kathryn Kuhlman to feed on today

00:42:45.800 --> 00:42:47.630
before I did my broadcast,

00:42:47.640 --> 00:42:49.670
listening to old tent

00:42:49.680 --> 00:42:51.710
revivals from Oral Roberts and just

00:42:51.720 --> 00:42:55.750
feeding on the past and going, 'Man, when's

00:42:55.760 --> 00:42:58.390
our

00:42:58.390 --> 00:42:58.400
time?'And

00:42:58.400 --> 00:43:01.190
there has to be our time.

00:43:01.200 --> 00:43:04.630
I truly believe we're about to see the

00:43:04.640 --> 00:43:06.910
greatest harvest of souls this world has

00:43:06.920 --> 00:43:08.830
ever seen before. But it's not going to

00:43:08.840 --> 00:43:11.670
be something that we've seen before. He's

00:43:11.680 --> 00:43:13.470
going to do something that's never been

00:43:13.480 --> 00:43:15.430
seen before. Behold, he's going to do

00:43:15.440 --> 00:43:17.350
something new.

00:43:17.360 --> 00:43:19.510
But I told the Lord, I said, 'I don't

00:43:19.520 --> 00:43:21.910
want to focus on what people that are old,

00:43:21.910 --> 00:43:21.920
that

00:43:21.920 --> 00:43:24.190
have passed on, that are no longer

00:43:24.200 --> 00:43:27.030
here, did. I want to see something new in

00:43:27.040 --> 00:43:29.110
this generation.

00:43:29.120 --> 00:43:30.670
I want to see it with my sons, with my

00:43:30.680 --> 00:43:33.030
daughters, with the youth

00:43:33.040 --> 00:43:35.230
of this generation, with our young

00:43:35.240 --> 00:43:37.190
people.

00:43:37.200 --> 00:43:40.950
God, pour out your spirit one more time.

00:43:40.960 --> 00:43:43.990
Cause a major revival to flow over

00:43:44.000 --> 00:43:46.550
America. You said you were not done with

00:43:46.550 --> 00:43:46.560
America.'And

00:43:46.560 --> 00:43:48.990
this is not a revival

00:43:48.990 --> 00:43:49.000
where

00:43:49.000 --> 00:43:51.630
we go, 'Well, we rededicated America back

00:43:51.640 --> 00:43:54.030
to God.'I don't care about America being

00:43:54.040 --> 00:43:56.310
back to God; I want the church of

00:43:56.320 --> 00:43:59.230
America to be rededicated without

00:43:59.240 --> 00:44:03.230
this lukewarm church that I see.

00:44:03.240 --> 00:44:05.350
When

00:44:07.240 --> 00:44:09.510
you

00:44:09.520 --> 00:44:12.470
visit a church and you walk away not

00:44:12.480 --> 00:44:13.950
feeling

00:44:13.960 --> 00:44:15.670
stirred up,

00:44:15.680 --> 00:44:17.790
not feeling that you've got what it

00:44:17.800 --> 00:44:20.070
takes to conquer the week. When you walk

00:44:20.080 --> 00:44:21.830
away and you go, 'Well, that was a real

00:44:21.840 --> 00:44:24.790
good little whatever,'and you had some

00:44:24.800 --> 00:44:26.230
beautiful praise and worship because

00:44:26.230 --> 00:44:26.240
you've

00:44:26.240 --> 00:44:27.910
got paid

00:44:27.920 --> 00:44:29.870
musicians up there that are getting

00:44:29.880 --> 00:44:31.830
paid some of them almost six

00:44:31.840 --> 00:44:34.350
figures playing up there because they're

00:44:34.360 --> 00:44:36.310
trained

00:44:36.320 --> 00:44:38.070
musicians that are

00:44:38.080 --> 00:44:39.790
in it for the money

00:44:39.800 --> 00:44:41.710
and everything. I know a man's

00:44:41.720 --> 00:44:43.230
worthy of his hire, I'm not trying to

00:44:43.240 --> 00:44:46.310
always criticize, but I'm wanting to

00:44:46.320 --> 00:44:49.790
really emphasize: where is the true

00:44:49.800 --> 00:44:52.630
Holy Ghost church

00:44:52.640 --> 00:44:55.710
where we see the power of God flow

00:44:55.720 --> 00:44:57.350
through the auditorium and people

00:44:57.360 --> 00:44:59.950
delivered from demonic oppression and

00:44:59.960 --> 00:45:02.230
possession and the spirit of the Lord

00:45:02.230 --> 00:45:02.240
heals

00:45:02.240 --> 00:45:03.670
them from the top of their head to

00:45:03.680 --> 00:45:07.390
the soles of their feet?

00:45:07.400 --> 00:45:10.750
It's a fire shut up in my bones.

00:45:10.760 --> 00:45:13.230
And I hear some people when we talk

00:45:13.230 --> 00:45:13.240
to—because

00:45:13.240 --> 00:45:15.150
I love the South Koreans, they're

00:45:15.160 --> 00:45:17.750
some of the most beautiful-hearted

00:45:17.760 --> 00:45:19.750
praying people. I mean, my goodness,

00:45:19.760 --> 00:45:21.990
they're good folks. I love my South

00:45:22.000 --> 00:45:23.270
Korean channel.

00:45:23.280 --> 00:45:25.070
And it's amazing what the Lord has

00:45:25.080 --> 00:45:27.270
done over in South Korea with the

00:45:27.280 --> 00:45:29.990
people. They're so hungry.

00:45:30.000 --> 00:45:31.950
And

00:45:31.960 --> 00:45:35.950
I just look for the authentic.

00:45:35.960 --> 00:45:37.190
And then some of them say,

00:45:37.190 --> 00:45:37.200
'Braden,

00:45:37.200 --> 00:45:38.870
we're experiencing that

00:45:38.870 --> 00:45:38.880
here.'We're

00:45:38.880 --> 00:45:41.030
experiencing it in Africa; there

00:45:41.030 --> 00:45:41.040
are

00:45:41.040 --> 00:45:43.110
parts of Africa where we're experiencing

00:45:43.120 --> 00:45:45.030
that. We get the emails. We're seeing

00:45:45.040 --> 00:45:47.190
revival. We're seeing this.

00:45:47.200 --> 00:45:48.830
Are you all not seeing anything like

00:45:48.840 --> 00:45:50.590
that? People are being raised from the

00:45:50.600 --> 00:45:52.990
dead. People are being healed.

00:45:52.990 --> 00:45:53.000
Blind

00:45:53.000 --> 00:45:54.950
eyes are opening. We're seeing those

00:45:54.960 --> 00:45:57.070
things. Are you not seeing that in

00:45:57.080 --> 00:45:58.910
America?

00:45:58.920 --> 00:46:00.830
I said,

00:46:00.840 --> 00:46:03.870
'No, I don't think so.

00:46:03.880 --> 00:46:07.990
I don't see it in the circle we're in.

00:46:08.000 --> 00:46:09.510
But if it is happening, I want to be a

00:46:09.520 --> 00:46:11.870
part of it.

00:46:11.880 --> 00:46:13.590
I know I see some miracles that my friend,

00:46:13.600 --> 00:46:16.070
Billy Burke—he has healing

00:46:16.070 --> 00:46:16.080
services—but

00:46:16.080 --> 00:46:17.910
it's not like what I want to

00:46:17.910 --> 00:46:17.920
see:

00:46:17.920 --> 00:46:20.910
Acts chapter 2—raise the dead, walking

00:46:20.920 --> 00:46:23.150
on water. I mean, you know, I want to

00:46:23.160 --> 00:46:24.630
see some of that.

00:46:24.640 --> 00:46:25.910
I love it when people get healed of

00:46:25.920 --> 00:46:27.670
cancer and people's eyes get opened. It's

00:46:27.680 --> 00:46:30.030
amazing. Never lose your awe of God,

00:46:30.040 --> 00:46:33.030
but I'm wanting creative miracles: arms

00:46:33.040 --> 00:46:35.390
growing out, eyes popping back in, ears

00:46:35.400 --> 00:46:37.470
that weren't there, appendages that were

00:46:37.480 --> 00:46:39.310
not there coming back like the

00:46:39.320 --> 00:46:41.190
disciples.'And

00:46:41.200 --> 00:46:42.310
people are saying, 'Brandon, we're

00:46:42.320 --> 00:46:43.750
having that over here.'And I thought,

00:46:43.760 --> 00:46:45.590
'What do we get to take in America? How

00:46:45.600 --> 00:46:48.790
do we have

00:46:48.790 --> 00:46:48.800
that?'I

00:46:48.800 --> 00:46:54.070
am on a mission.

00:46:54.080 --> 00:46:57.310
I was cleaning out my garage and

00:46:57.320 --> 00:46:59.270
blowing out the leaves from

00:46:59.280 --> 00:47:01.790
the winter and doing things, and the

00:47:01.790 --> 00:47:01.800
Lord

00:47:01.800 --> 00:47:03.910
stirred in my

00:47:03.920 --> 00:47:06.230
spirit: 'What does it take to see the

00:47:06.240 --> 00:47:07.830
dead raised when you need to see it

00:47:07.840 --> 00:47:11.550
raised?

00:47:11.560 --> 00:47:13.990
When you see somebody you

00:47:14.000 --> 00:47:16.270
love die

00:47:16.280 --> 00:47:18.310
or they're not here anymore and you

00:47:18.320 --> 00:47:21.310
know that there's Lazarus

00:47:21.320 --> 00:47:23.430
moments coming,

00:47:23.440 --> 00:47:25.590
that though you were dead yet shall you

00:47:25.600 --> 00:47:26.750
live.'When

00:47:26.760 --> 00:47:29.270
there's an anointing that needs to

00:47:29.280 --> 00:47:32.990
be pulled on and you see desperation in

00:47:33.000 --> 00:47:36.790
someone's eyes, is it there to

00:47:36.800 --> 00:47:39.030
bring forth the miracle that they're

00:47:39.040 --> 00:47:40.750
believing for, to pull on that

00:47:40.760 --> 00:47:44.430
anointing?

00:47:44.440 --> 00:47:47.430
What does it take?

00:47:47.440 --> 00:47:49.470
And I go over things that I hear my

00:47:49.480 --> 00:47:51.510
elder generals talk about, like Billy and

00:47:51.520 --> 00:47:53.470
Billy, both

00:47:53.470 --> 00:47:53.480
Billies,

00:47:53.480 --> 00:47:55.550
and they talk about the sufferings

00:47:55.560 --> 00:47:57.510
and sharing His

00:47:57.520 --> 00:47:59.390
suffering and the greater glory

00:47:59.400 --> 00:48:01.150
and things that are attached to it.

00:48:01.160 --> 00:48:04.150
And I just go, 'Lord, show me.

00:48:04.160 --> 00:48:06.910
What is the switch

00:48:06.920 --> 00:48:10.550
to flip on the light in the darkness,

00:48:10.560 --> 00:48:12.550
that Your light is shining on our

00:48:12.560 --> 00:48:16.870
face like Moses,

00:48:16.880 --> 00:48:18.390
that when they see us, we're

00:48:18.400 --> 00:48:20.510
wall-to-wall Holy Ghost?'But it's not

00:48:20.520 --> 00:48:22.110
just something that we confess and we're

00:48:22.120 --> 00:48:25.270
parroting something, but it's actual

00:48:25.280 --> 00:48:26.950
manifestation

00:48:26.960 --> 00:48:29.350
that when we walk in the room, the

00:48:29.360 --> 00:48:32.230
shadow touches and they're healed and

00:48:32.240 --> 00:48:35.870
they rise up and walk.

00:48:35.880 --> 00:48:37.710
When the anointing that was on the

00:48:37.720 --> 00:48:40.990
disciples is tangible on

00:48:41.000 --> 00:48:42.510
us

00:48:42.520 --> 00:48:44.150
and it's not something that we just

00:48:44.160 --> 00:48:46.910
experience once, but we walk in it on a

00:48:46.920 --> 00:48:51.030
day-to-day basis.

00:48:51.040 --> 00:48:53.710
What is it that takes that? Is it

00:48:53.720 --> 00:48:55.430
the persecution? Because when I was praying

00:48:55.440 --> 00:48:57.510
for Africa

00:48:57.520 --> 00:48:59.070
and we were on here praying and we

00:48:59.080 --> 00:49:01.150
saw the people of Nigeria, I believe

00:49:01.160 --> 00:49:03.430
it was, and I saw their flag, and the

00:49:03.440 --> 00:49:05.550
Lord said, 'The greater the persecution,

00:49:05.560 --> 00:49:08.630
the greater the anointing.

00:49:08.640 --> 00:49:11.350
The greater the persecution, the

00:49:11.360 --> 00:49:14.230
greater the presence and the power and

00:49:14.240 --> 00:49:16.270
the glory comes with the

00:49:16.280 --> 00:49:18.550
anointing.

00:49:18.560 --> 00:49:21.310
For these sufferings bring forth the

00:49:21.320 --> 00:49:25.590
greater

00:49:25.600 --> 00:49:29.030
glory.'When

00:49:29.040 --> 00:49:30.510
Paul and

00:49:30.520 --> 00:49:32.630
Silas... Peter was in the prison, and then

00:49:32.640 --> 00:49:35.710
you have these moments

00:49:35.720 --> 00:49:39.910
where the church prayed

00:49:39.920 --> 00:49:42.390
and they interceded and they were able

00:49:42.400 --> 00:49:45.070
to get the gates opened.

00:49:45.080 --> 00:49:48.190
They were able, with guards on both sides

00:49:48.200 --> 00:49:50.270
watching over them in the middle of the

00:49:50.280 --> 00:49:52.830
prison. And they didn't want, because they

00:49:52.840 --> 00:49:55.230
knew that they had some kind of

00:49:55.240 --> 00:49:57.390
supernatural ability

00:49:57.400 --> 00:50:00.390
and they had been assigned these

00:50:00.400 --> 00:50:02.910
guards on both sides. And Peter's

00:50:02.920 --> 00:50:07.430
asleep

00:50:07.440 --> 00:50:10.790
knowing that tomorrow he's going to die.

00:50:10.800 --> 00:50:12.230
I don't know about you, but if I get

00:50:12.240 --> 00:50:14.270
some kind of bad report, it's hard

00:50:14.280 --> 00:50:15.790
to sleep sometimes. You go,

00:50:15.800 --> 00:50:17.670
'Oh, man,'because your mind's running.

00:50:17.680 --> 00:50:19.470
But you have so much confidence and

00:50:19.480 --> 00:50:21.510
you're so fully persuaded that you're in

00:50:21.520 --> 00:50:22.849
the prison

00:50:23.120 --> 00:50:24.870
and you're snoring and an

00:50:24.880 --> 00:50:26.550
angel has to wake you up:

00:50:26.560 --> 00:50:28.550
'Get up!

00:50:28.560 --> 00:50:31.750
Get up!'But the prayers of the

00:50:31.750 --> 00:50:31.760
saints—why

00:50:31.760 --> 00:50:34.670
we have this channel—the prayers

00:50:34.680 --> 00:50:37.390
of the early church had

00:50:37.400 --> 00:50:40.910
enough to get the guards knocked out,

00:50:40.920 --> 00:50:43.590
open the prison door,

00:50:43.600 --> 00:50:49.550
open the gate, and get him free.

00:50:49.560 --> 00:50:52.150
What kind of prayer, what kind of

00:50:52.160 --> 00:50:54.670
intercession does it take to open a

00:50:54.680 --> 00:50:56.750
gate?

00:50:56.760 --> 00:50:59.310
A supernatural opening of the gate?

00:50:59.320 --> 00:51:01.830
What kind of prayer does it take to open

00:51:01.840 --> 00:51:05.070
the prison door?

00:51:05.080 --> 00:51:06.790
When someone's wrongly being accused in

00:51:06.800 --> 00:51:08.790
these last days, what kind of prayer

00:51:08.800 --> 00:51:11.750
does it take for a church to bring forth

00:51:11.760 --> 00:51:13.750
just a little revival and some fire in

00:51:13.760 --> 00:51:16.150
your church?

00:51:16.160 --> 00:51:18.390
That it's not church usual, it's

00:51:18.400 --> 00:51:21.190
church unusual.

00:51:21.200 --> 00:51:22.950
And that's what I'm just like,

00:51:22.950 --> 00:51:22.960
because

00:51:22.960 --> 00:51:24.350
the Lord said, 'What

00:51:24.360 --> 00:51:25.630
are you looking for?'I said,

00:51:25.640 --> 00:51:28.750
'I'm looking for more.

00:51:28.760 --> 00:51:32.950
I'm not satisfied with the status quo. I

00:51:32.950 --> 00:51:32.960
am

00:51:32.960 --> 00:51:37.110
so done with church usual.

00:51:37.120 --> 00:51:39.350
I want church unusual.

00:51:39.360 --> 00:51:42.230
I want to see fire shut up in my bones.

00:51:42.240 --> 00:51:44.710
I want to see what Oral

00:51:44.720 --> 00:51:46.710
Roberts saw. And I want to see and

00:51:46.720 --> 00:51:48.350
experience more than what Kathryn

00:51:48.360 --> 00:51:53.790
Kuhlman experienced.

00:51:53.800 --> 00:51:55.390
If not,

00:51:55.400 --> 00:51:58.710
I said, if not, then why not? Why not me?

00:51:58.720 --> 00:52:00.710
Why then? What? You know, Lord, I

00:52:00.720 --> 00:52:02.350
know they went through things. I know

00:52:02.360 --> 00:52:04.230
I've been through some things, but Lord,

00:52:04.240 --> 00:52:07.670
what turns on that

00:52:07.680 --> 00:52:11.710
switch?

00:52:11.720 --> 00:52:13.270
Because the only thing that's ever going to

00:52:13.280 --> 00:52:15.510
change America

00:52:15.520 --> 00:52:17.550
is whenever the sons and the daughters,

00:52:17.560 --> 00:52:18.670
us,

00:52:18.680 --> 00:52:21.350
become who we're called to be and rise

00:52:21.360 --> 00:52:23.790
up and stop trying to just always pray

00:52:23.800 --> 00:52:26.310
for revival, but let revival start with

00:52:26.320 --> 00:52:27.550
us

00:52:27.560 --> 00:52:31.230
and say, 'Here am I, Lord. Send

00:52:31.230 --> 00:52:31.240
me.'But

00:52:31.240 --> 00:52:37.310
don't send me with no power.

00:52:37.320 --> 00:52:39.270
I want them to marvel at the ignorance

00:52:39.280 --> 00:52:41.190
of Brandon Biggs. Whenever he speaks, they

00:52:41.200 --> 00:52:43.350
go, 'He has been with

00:52:43.350 --> 00:52:43.360
Jesus.'There's

00:52:43.360 --> 00:52:47.350
something different about him.

00:52:47.360 --> 00:52:49.230
Why? It's not about giving glory to

00:52:49.240 --> 00:52:51.950
Brandon, but there's something different

00:52:51.960 --> 00:52:55.710
about what's on that man. And it's

00:52:55.720 --> 00:52:57.390
Jesus.

00:52:57.400 --> 00:53:00.030
Because he had been with Jesus.

00:53:00.040 --> 00:53:03.230
They marveled because they knew they

00:53:03.240 --> 00:53:05.670
were unlearned and ignorant men. But

00:53:05.680 --> 00:53:10.110
they knew they had been with Jesus.

00:53:10.120 --> 00:53:12.390
How'd they know that? Because the glory

00:53:12.400 --> 00:53:15.070
was there.

00:53:15.080 --> 00:53:18.350
The manifested presence was there.

00:53:18.360 --> 00:53:20.830
Because when God shows up on the scene,

00:53:20.840 --> 00:53:25.590
He changes the atmosphere.

00:53:25.600 --> 00:53:27.510
And when you go into a church and the

00:53:27.520 --> 00:53:30.590
atmosphere is dull, like touching a cold

00:53:30.600 --> 00:53:34.590
stove,

00:53:34.600 --> 00:53:37.990
and it's week after week...

00:53:38.000 --> 00:53:41.190
I'm not trying to pick at

00:53:41.200 --> 00:53:43.710
the church I used to work for, but week

00:53:43.720 --> 00:53:46.830
after week you go into a

00:53:46.840 --> 00:53:49.870
church and you go,

00:53:49.880 --> 00:53:52.950
'I work here. I get a check here, but it

00:53:52.960 --> 00:53:56.870
is dead as touching a cold

00:53:56.870 --> 00:53:56.880
stove.'And

00:53:56.880 --> 00:53:58.510
yet people are getting blessed by

00:53:58.520 --> 00:53:59.590
it because

00:53:59.590 --> 00:53:59.600
you've

00:53:59.600 --> 00:54:01.550
got somebody playing some good

00:54:01.560 --> 00:54:03.590
music or whatever

00:54:03.600 --> 00:54:06.190
sermons. Okay.

00:54:06.200 --> 00:54:08.990
But I go, 'Why are we playing

00:54:08.990 --> 00:54:09.000
church?'God

00:54:09.000 --> 00:54:13.030
came to save and set the captives

00:54:13.040 --> 00:54:16.390
free.

00:54:16.400 --> 00:54:19.150
'I come to save that which was

00:54:19.150 --> 00:54:19.160
lost.'And

00:54:19.160 --> 00:54:21.710
now in Acts 4, this is my

00:54:21.720 --> 00:54:24.270
favorite: 'Now when they saw the

00:54:24.280 --> 00:54:26.150
boldness

00:54:32.320 --> 00:54:35.550
of Peter and John, and perceived that

00:54:35.560 --> 00:54:38.470
they were unlearned and ignorant men,

00:54:38.480 --> 00:54:41.910
they marveled and took knowledge of them

00:54:41.920 --> 00:54:47.150
that they had been with

00:54:47.150 --> 00:54:47.160
Jesus.'It's

00:54:47.160 --> 00:54:51.390
not just being with Him one time.

00:54:51.400 --> 00:54:54.870
It's being with Him day after day,

00:54:54.880 --> 00:54:59.310
sitting at His feet and

00:54:59.320 --> 00:55:02.350
having a relationship with Him. I

00:55:02.360 --> 00:55:04.750
told you more people would go home.

00:55:04.760 --> 00:55:07.710
James Robison went home yesterday.

00:55:07.720 --> 00:55:10.150
We have more generals going home.

00:55:10.160 --> 00:55:11.390
And the Lord said there will be a

00:55:11.400 --> 00:55:13.430
changing of the guard, a passing of the

00:55:13.440 --> 00:55:15.990
baton in the days ahead. And you're going to

00:55:16.000 --> 00:55:16.910
see

00:55:16.910 --> 00:55:16.920
the

00:55:16.920 --> 00:55:19.670
major generals that have been in the

00:55:19.680 --> 00:55:25.310
past start to transition home.

00:55:25.320 --> 00:55:26.950
He said, 'I'm raising up new voices. I'm

00:55:26.960 --> 00:55:28.710
raising up a new generation. I'm raising

00:55:28.720 --> 00:55:31.230
up new generals

00:55:31.240 --> 00:55:33.950
to those that I've called that say,

00:55:33.960 --> 00:55:36.230
"Yes, here am I, Lord, send

00:55:36.230 --> 00:55:36.240
me."You're

00:55:36.240 --> 00:55:37.950
the

00:55:37.950 --> 00:55:37.960
closers.'They

00:55:37.960 --> 00:55:39.310
had their time and this generation

00:55:39.310 --> 00:55:39.320
is

00:55:39.320 --> 00:55:40.870
going to start to go home.

00:55:40.880 --> 00:55:41.990
And the Lord said, 'You're going to see

00:55:42.000 --> 00:55:44.150
more and more of it through the

00:55:44.150 --> 00:55:44.160
summer.'We

00:55:44.160 --> 00:55:45.750
just had another one,

00:55:45.750 --> 00:55:45.760
a

00:55:45.760 --> 00:55:48.510
third one: Marilyn Hickey, Joni, and

00:55:48.520 --> 00:55:49.670
now

00:55:49.670 --> 00:55:49.680
Pat—and

00:55:49.680 --> 00:55:52.910
I

00:55:52.910 --> 00:55:52.920
only

00:55:52.920 --> 00:55:53.910
say, 'Well, who's

00:55:53.910 --> 00:55:53.920
next?'I

00:55:53.920 --> 00:55:55.790
don't know.

00:55:55.800 --> 00:55:57.150
But there are going to be more

00:55:57.160 --> 00:55:58.950
transitions.

00:55:58.960 --> 00:56:01.870
I saw certain major ministries

00:56:01.880 --> 00:56:05.510
going home. Some of them huge,

00:56:05.520 --> 00:56:08.790
huge ministries. And it will get world

00:56:08.800 --> 00:56:11.110
attention.

00:56:11.120 --> 00:56:12.990
Huge. And Pat Robertson was a huge

00:56:13.000 --> 00:56:16.470
ministry.

00:56:16.480 --> 00:56:18.030
Joni, I mean, they're all pretty... they

00:56:18.040 --> 00:56:19.470
were all pretty big

00:56:19.470 --> 00:56:19.480
ministries."Marilyn

00:56:19.480 --> 00:56:21.630
Hickey, all of them.

00:56:21.640 --> 00:56:26.270
So, we see a transition.

00:56:29.560 --> 00:56:32.630
When people step out and go home,

00:56:32.640 --> 00:56:36.350
there's a void. One needs to rise up.

00:56:36.360 --> 00:56:39.830
Will you be that person?

00:56:39.840 --> 00:56:41.590
They're up there rooting for us right

00:56:41.600 --> 00:56:42.550
now.

00:56:42.550 --> 00:56:42.560
Their

00:56:42.560 --> 00:56:44.590
cloud of witnesses say, 'Will

00:56:44.600 --> 00:56:47.310
you help finish the race?

00:56:47.320 --> 00:56:52.030
Don't let the baton drop. Keep running

00:56:52.040 --> 00:56:58.230
with this end-time

00:56:58.230 --> 00:56:58.240
army.'And

00:56:58.240 --> 00:57:00.390
I know there's more going home

00:57:00.400 --> 00:57:02.910
soon. The Lord said it; He told me. He

00:57:02.920 --> 00:57:05.070
said specific ones to me, and I've

00:57:05.070 --> 00:57:05.080
never—don't

00:57:05.080 --> 00:57:08.950
make that public.

00:57:08.960 --> 00:57:11.350
So I just want to stir you up today to

00:57:11.350 --> 00:57:11.360
not

00:57:11.360 --> 00:57:13.070
give up on your dreams of what

00:57:13.080 --> 00:57:15.270
God's called you to do just because you

00:57:15.280 --> 00:57:16.990
didn't see it manifest in the first

00:57:17.000 --> 00:57:20.430
years of when you thought it should.

00:57:20.440 --> 00:57:22.710
God knows when you're able to handle it,

00:57:22.720 --> 00:57:25.070
and when the time is, and when

00:57:25.080 --> 00:57:27.070
it's time for you to rise up and be who

00:57:27.080 --> 00:57:28.790
you need to be.

00:57:28.800 --> 00:57:31.390
Humble yourself. Even if it's to say,

00:57:31.400 --> 00:57:32.910
'Hey, I'm going to go volunteer at a

00:57:32.920 --> 00:57:35.710
church and be a janitor.

00:57:35.720 --> 00:57:38.710
Do whatever it takes to get the gospel

00:57:38.710 --> 00:57:38.720
out.'Diana,

00:57:38.720 --> 00:57:40.390
we were talking about

00:57:40.400 --> 00:57:42.710
it when we worked at the church. The guest

00:57:42.720 --> 00:57:43.950
speaker

00:57:43.960 --> 00:57:46.790
usually gets the most praise.

00:57:49.880 --> 00:57:54.230
They get in late, they leave early.

00:57:54.240 --> 00:57:56.230
The janitor, like me—I was cleaning the

00:57:56.240 --> 00:57:58.470
bathrooms until sometimes 1:00 or 2:00 in

00:57:58.480 --> 00:58:00.790
the morning after the service. You

00:58:00.790 --> 00:58:00.800
go

00:58:00.800 --> 00:58:02.990
in there and it's dark.

00:58:03.000 --> 00:58:05.190
It's like crickets,

00:58:05.200 --> 00:58:07.070
and you set up the chairs, you vacuum

00:58:07.080 --> 00:58:08.310
the aisles, you're making sure all the

00:58:08.320 --> 00:58:09.350
diapers are cleaned out of the

00:58:09.360 --> 00:58:10.750
nurseries,

00:58:10.760 --> 00:58:12.310
and you do that

00:58:12.320 --> 00:58:15.070
time and time again—the least thanked

00:58:15.080 --> 00:58:17.830
position.

00:58:17.840 --> 00:58:20.910
But without that janitor, without that

00:58:20.920 --> 00:58:24.590
offering counter, without the usher,

00:58:24.600 --> 00:58:26.710
without the greeter, without the parking

00:58:26.720 --> 00:58:28.470
lot attendant,

00:58:28.480 --> 00:58:30.750
without the nursery worker,

00:58:30.760 --> 00:58:33.110
that guest speaker or whoever it was for

00:58:33.120 --> 00:58:36.070
the revival couldn't have gotten the

00:58:36.080 --> 00:58:38.550
job done the way they did.

00:58:38.550 --> 00:58:38.560
Because

00:58:38.560 --> 00:58:40.790
if the bathrooms were stinky,

00:58:40.800 --> 00:58:43.070
the floors had urine on them, somebody

00:58:43.080 --> 00:58:45.710
just took a dump all over the stool,

00:58:45.710 --> 00:58:45.720
you've

00:58:45.720 --> 00:58:48.750
got all this nasty stuff going on,

00:58:48.760 --> 00:58:50.310
and you're going, 'This is the

00:58:50.320 --> 00:58:54.070
stinkiest bathroom I ever walked

00:58:54.070 --> 00:58:54.080
in,'and

00:58:54.080 --> 00:58:55.630
you go, 'I don't even want

00:58:55.640 --> 00:58:57.190
to go into that church and listen to

00:58:57.200 --> 00:59:00.110
this

00:59:00.110 --> 00:59:00.120
guy.'Don't

00:59:00.120 --> 00:59:02.870
ever underestimate the importance

00:59:02.880 --> 00:59:04.910
of who you are

00:59:04.920 --> 00:59:08.070
and how you bring forth the atmosphere

00:59:08.080 --> 00:59:10.710
for that person to receive what Jesus is

00:59:10.720 --> 00:59:12.630
about to speak through that

00:59:12.640 --> 00:59:15.630
speaker. Your part was just as important

00:59:15.640 --> 00:59:18.190
as the speaker's was.

00:59:18.200 --> 00:59:20.750
And I remember setting up the chairs,

00:59:20.760 --> 00:59:22.630
cleaning up the vomit

00:59:22.640 --> 00:59:24.470
when somebody wrote poo on the

00:59:24.480 --> 00:59:26.110
wall,

00:59:26.120 --> 00:59:28.870
wipe their booty on my wall and

00:59:28.880 --> 00:59:30.750
write it out in

00:59:30.750 --> 00:59:30.760
numbers—'poo'or

00:59:30.760 --> 00:59:32.590
whatever they want to say, just

00:59:32.600 --> 00:59:36.030
being disgusting with their feces,

00:59:36.040 --> 00:59:37.750
doing some of the most

00:59:37.760 --> 00:59:39.910
filthy, vile things I've ever seen in a

00:59:39.920 --> 00:59:41.270
bathroom.

00:59:41.280 --> 00:59:45.350
I cleaned it for 15 years of my life.

00:59:45.360 --> 00:59:48.470
And I remember every single time going

00:59:48.480 --> 00:59:51.230
home and thinking, 'Man, I just wanted

00:59:51.240 --> 00:59:53.270
to make it where if they came in and it

00:59:53.280 --> 00:59:55.350
smelled good,

00:59:55.360 --> 00:59:56.990
if they walked into the bathroom and it

00:59:57.000 --> 00:59:59.150
didn't smell like

00:59:59.160 --> 01:00:00.470
stuff

01:00:00.480 --> 01:00:02.870
or nurseries or whatever and their kids

01:00:02.880 --> 01:00:04.750
didn't go home sick and they said,

01:00:04.750 --> 01:00:04.760
"Our

01:00:04.760 --> 01:00:07.110
kids always come to church and

01:00:07.120 --> 01:00:08.830
play on the church equipment and they're

01:00:08.840 --> 01:00:10.950
always leaving with a cold or a virus

01:00:10.960 --> 01:00:13.230
because they spread it around."'I kept

01:00:13.240 --> 01:00:15.870
even the church

01:00:16.520 --> 01:00:19.590
nursery toys clean with bleach and

01:00:19.600 --> 01:00:21.510
whatever, making sure they didn't spread

01:00:21.520 --> 01:00:24.390
viruses around during flu season.

01:00:24.400 --> 01:00:26.790
Always trying to think outside the box.

01:00:26.800 --> 01:00:28.950
If my kid was in here,

01:00:28.960 --> 01:00:30.990
how do you make sure that the virus

01:00:31.000 --> 01:00:32.630
from these flu bugs kids are passing

01:00:32.640 --> 01:00:34.150
around

01:00:34.160 --> 01:00:37.030
stays out?

01:00:37.040 --> 01:00:40.670
Always going the extra mile,

01:00:40.680 --> 01:00:42.390
making it so if you don't show up,

01:00:42.400 --> 01:00:46.430
they're going to notice.

01:00:46.440 --> 01:00:48.910
And there's many of you that may do

01:00:48.920 --> 01:00:50.630
that right now at your church. And I'm

01:00:50.640 --> 01:00:52.750
telling you, it's all hands on deck.

01:00:52.760 --> 01:00:56.310
Never ever take your position of what

01:00:56.320 --> 01:00:59.630
God's called you to do lightly.

01:00:59.640 --> 01:01:02.150
For if it wasn't for people like you,

01:01:02.160 --> 01:01:04.110
the job wouldn't be done as effective as

01:01:04.120 --> 01:01:06.230
it should have been.

01:01:06.240 --> 01:01:08.950
And I'm trying to tell you right now, the

01:01:08.960 --> 01:01:11.510
same reward that the person's

01:01:11.520 --> 01:01:13.150
going to get up there preaching with the

01:01:13.150 --> 01:01:13.160
fire—you

01:01:13.160 --> 01:01:14.830
think, 'Oh boy, they've got

01:01:14.840 --> 01:01:17.270
it all

01:01:17.270 --> 01:01:17.280
made'—man,

01:01:17.280 --> 01:01:19.630
great is the reward of those that do

01:01:19.640 --> 01:01:21.910
what we've done.

01:01:21.920 --> 01:01:23.550
The person who counts the offerings, the

01:01:23.560 --> 01:01:25.630
person who makes sure the bills are

01:01:25.640 --> 01:01:26.790
paid

01:01:26.800 --> 01:01:28.230
so that the lights are on when they

01:01:28.240 --> 01:01:30.430
showed up,

01:01:30.440 --> 01:01:32.310
making sure the water bill was paid so

01:01:32.320 --> 01:01:35.110
the toilet would flush.

01:01:35.120 --> 01:01:37.470
Never take for granted what God has

01:01:37.480 --> 01:01:39.790
called you to do and do it with all your

01:01:39.800 --> 01:01:42.870
heart.

01:01:42.880 --> 01:01:44.750
That's what we did and we continue to

01:01:44.760 --> 01:01:46.230
do.

01:01:46.240 --> 01:01:48.310
I still feel like I'm the janitor. I

01:01:48.320 --> 01:01:50.590
still feel like my wife is the

01:01:50.600 --> 01:01:53.030
offering counter and the

01:01:53.040 --> 01:01:55.510
data entry person, always

01:01:55.520 --> 01:01:57.630
behind the scenes trying just to make

01:01:57.640 --> 01:02:02.030
it.

01:02:02.040 --> 01:02:04.670
Be thankful for where you are and know

01:02:04.680 --> 01:02:06.430
that your reward is great when you get

01:02:06.440 --> 01:02:08.510
on the other side.

01:02:08.520 --> 01:02:12.070
Keep your head up.

01:02:12.080 --> 01:02:13.750
And that's my message for what I felt in

01:02:13.760 --> 01:02:15.350
my heart tonight.

01:02:15.360 --> 01:02:19.790
I said, 'Lord, what is it going to take?

01:02:19.800 --> 01:02:24.070
I'm so hungry for authentic.

01:02:24.080 --> 01:02:26.510
I'm so hungry, desperate for a true

01:02:26.520 --> 01:02:32.110
move of God.'And I'm so tired of

01:02:32.110 --> 01:02:32.120
parrots—parrots

01:02:32.120 --> 01:02:34.430
on the internet, parrots with

01:02:34.440 --> 01:02:36.310
people that just say

01:02:36.320 --> 01:02:37.790
something because they heard it from a Jack

01:02:37.790 --> 01:02:37.800
Coe

01:02:37.800 --> 01:02:40.070
meeting and you look at it and you

01:02:40.080 --> 01:02:43.030
go, 'That's truly not who you

01:02:43.030 --> 01:02:43.040
are.'And

01:02:43.040 --> 01:02:47.150
you are really

01:02:47.160 --> 01:02:49.350
fake.

01:02:49.360 --> 01:02:51.590
I want to see signs; follow them that

01:02:51.600 --> 01:02:54.110
believe.

01:02:54.120 --> 01:02:56.550
So, I stay in my little place where

01:02:56.560 --> 01:02:57.910
I'm at.

01:02:57.920 --> 01:02:59.390
You know, a lot of people invite me to

01:02:59.400 --> 01:03:01.110
go do a lot of stuff. I've had some of

01:03:01.120 --> 01:03:02.870
the biggest businessmen, some of the

01:03:02.880 --> 01:03:05.270
richest people in the United States or

01:03:05.280 --> 01:03:07.670
world contact me.

01:03:07.670 --> 01:03:07.680
And

01:03:07.680 --> 01:03:09.830
I don't know

01:03:09.840 --> 01:03:11.670
what to do with some of this. 'What am

01:03:11.680 --> 01:03:14.790
I? I'm just Brandon.'They

01:03:14.790 --> 01:03:14.800
tell me,

01:03:14.800 --> 01:03:16.150
'Brandon, you got to watch

01:03:16.160 --> 01:03:18.990
it. You got big politicians watching you

01:03:19.000 --> 01:03:21.190
all the

01:03:21.190 --> 01:03:21.200
time—senators

01:03:21.200 --> 01:03:24.430
and governors and

01:03:24.430 --> 01:03:24.440
mayors.'And

01:03:24.440 --> 01:03:29.630
I'm like, 'Why?

01:03:29.640 --> 01:03:32.510
I'm just

01:03:32.510 --> 01:03:32.520
Brandon.'And

01:03:32.520 --> 01:03:34.310
I always stay—the Lord always says,

01:03:34.320 --> 01:03:36.750
'Stay small in your own eyes. Never get a

01:03:36.760 --> 01:03:39.230
